about_the_job:
Job Description:

Responsible for the design and development of back-end systems for financial services to support Sea businesses worldwide.
Develop security, high reliability and complex transaction systems for financial business; handle concurrent processing scenarios with smooth user experience
Defining flexible and adaptable system function modules and deployment schemes for different business scenarios, physical environments and regulatory requirements
Responsible for mentoring the back-end team, tackling the technical difficulties of the systems, and overseeing project delivery and quality


Requirements:

Bachelor degree or above, more than 5 years of backend development experience, more than 1 year of team management experience;
Proficiency in at least one of Golang/Python/C++/Java; proficient in common data structures, algorithms and multi-threading technology;
Familiar with MySQL/Oracle and other database and common performance optimization methods
Familiar with middleware components such as Redis, HBase, Kafka;
Familiar with distributed architecture; familiar with microservice frameworks such as K8S; familiar with network protocols such as TCP/HTTPS; familiar with data exchange formats such as XML/JSON/ProtoBuf;
Experience in financial system development is preferred, and experience in high-concurrency system development is preferred.
